reviews_data.review_text: Stopped by at 615pm on a Saturday and they were closed when Google states that they close at 9pm. I've seen other reviews stating similar stories, kinda aggravating from the customer perspective but they won't have to worry about me coming again

El personal nos atendió excelente y hablaba español. Pedí el gelato de ferrero con hazelnut y sabor estaba delicioso y cremoso. El lugar es muy tranquilo con una decoración hermosa. Tuvimos una gran experiencia y deseo volver 🍦🇮🇹

reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Christina, thank you for your feedback. I want to sincerely apologize for the frustration caused. We were unfortunately the victims of a break-in yesterday and had to close unexpectedly for emergency window repairs. In the chaos of dealing with the police and securing the store, we were unable to update our online hours or answer the phone in time. We are very sorry you had to go through the hassle of getting a refund, and we hope you can understand this was an exceptional and difficult situation for us.
reviews_data.review_text: Twice now that I’ve ordered from their website because the store says open online and then I go to pick it up and the store is closed. They do not answer their phone when I try to call for help. I then have to call door dash directly and ask for a refund. They should not be accepting orders if they don’t have anyone working.

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the love on our gelato! We announce our daily hours on social media to keep everyone updated. This is just a temporary winter schedule, and we can't wait to get back to normal hours soon. Hugs!
reviews_data.review_text: Best ice cream but absurd how early they close and will randomly decide day of their hours without notice.
Very nice sweet people. Delicious desserts recommend coming here!
Great place with a big portions, got two scoops and it's enough for two ppl

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks Sean! We appreciate it!! Big hug!
reviews_data.review_text: Best Gelato in Charlotte, no competition. I drive an hour just to go there. Worth it.

reviews_data.owner_answer:
WOW! Thank you so much for this absolutely amazing review! 💖 Hearing that we are your favorite and the most authentic Italian gelato you can find truly means the world to us. 🇮🇹

We are so glad you love the flavors, the vibe, and the wonderful team here. We can't wait to welcome you back for more treats!

The Tutti Gelato Team 💛
reviews_data.review_text:
Tutti Gelato is my absolute favorite gelateria! 🍨 It’s the most authentic, delicious Italian gelato you’ll find anywhere. Whenever I’m in the area, I have to stop by—the flavors are rich, creamy, and unique, unlike any other place.

The owners are incredibly kind and welcoming, and you can sense the love they put into their shop. The décor is adorable too—perfect for cute, aesthetic photos!

I completely love this place and highly recommend it to anyone who wants authentic Italian gelato and great vibes. 💛🇮🇹

There was a sign on the door: get the code from the cashier, it will be on your receipt (or something like that). So we ran to the cashier, got the code after a few minutes, rushed back to the door, and couldn't open it! Meanwhile, my child really needed to use the restroom. reviews_data.review_text: Loved this place a million times than Jenny’s

We tried pistachio, stracciatella, chocolate sorbet & hazelnut. Also had a cortado & an espresso. SUPER tasty.

I have been here twice, and each have exceeded my expectations infinitely! The employees are very nice, and are very courteous toward its customers! There are about 16 gelato flavors, including: Tiramisu, Coffee, Feero Rocher, Dark Chocolate, Salted Caramel, Pistachio, Lemon Tart, Mint Chocolate Chip, Vanilla, and more! Their prices are more expensive than American ice cream; 2 scoops is $7, but it is SO worth it! It is many times better than Jeni’s Splendid Ice Cream (sorry for any misspellings), and I will absolutely be back here, and in greater numbers! They do not have a lot of parking, but there are bathrooms, many beverages like espresso shots, and even a free water pitcher! Tutti Gelato is by far my favorite ice cream/gelato place and will continue to be for a long time! Please, if you are in town, stop by Tutti Gelato! An authentic, Italian gelato parlor with a variety of flavors and beverages!
Delicious gelato!! Amazingly creamy

Tutti Gelato is a sweet escape! With a wide range of delicious flavors and creamy textures, every scoop is a delight. The cheerful ambiance and friendly staff make it the perfect spot to satisfy your sweet cravings. Don't miss out on this delightful gem!

reviews_data.review_text: Perfect place to get a scoop of gelato. Soo decadent you will only need one scoop. The ones of us who got 2 scoops had a tough time finishing them not because of size but because they were so decadent and sweet it satisfied our chocolate and sweet tooth cravings.  So many flavors to choose from with endless combinations if you want. The place was clean with plenty of seating. The moped photo op was fun to check out and get a few photos on. Great place to stop if you're in the area walking around or don't want to wait in the ridiculous lines for Jeni's. One of my top gelato choices in Charlotte.

The decor was so cute, staff was polite and helpful, and the gelato was SO delicious. even the presentation was great! My only wish was that the take-home bowls were in more sizes, lol! we live about an hour away and only were able to take home a pint, but we'd love a bigger size in the future! give it a try, you won't regret it.

Tutti gelato has been serving up delicious gelato in the heart of town. The owners are passionate about using fresh, local ingredients to create their gelato, and it shows in the taste. Tutti gelato also offers a variety of toppings, including fresh fruit, nuts, and chocolate chips.

In addition to its delicious gelato, Tutti gelato also has a warm and welcoming atmosphere. The staff is friendly and helpful, and they are always happy to chat with customers about their favorite flavors. Tutti gelato is the perfect place to stop for a quick treat on a hot day, or to enjoy a leisurely afternoon with friends.

Here are some of the things that customers love about Tutti gelato:

The gelato is made with fresh, local ingredients.

The gelato is churned slowly to create a smooth, creamy texture.

There are a wide variety of flavors to choose from.

The staff is friendly and helpful.

The atmosphere is warm and welcoming.

If you are looking for a delicious and satisfying gelato experience, then Tutti gelato is the place for you.
Very clean and very friendly. A lot of choices. Was delicious

I can't remember the flavor we got, but we got 2 scoops of two different flavors and also were able to sample 2 flavors (the one downside), but of all the ones we tasted, I already had my mind made up when I saw the flavors. Definitely delicious, and definitely recommend!

Creamy and delicious gelatos! We used to live in Italy, so an amazing gelato is always a great find! Whenever my husband and I visit new places, it’s a quest for us to try a highly-rated gelato establishment. I know that I would never find the same gelato here in the states as what we used to enjoy in Italy but this place comes close in decadence and silky smooth texture. It’s sweeter than its local Italian counterpart, but I think it is perfect for the average American palate. I had the Amaretto Disarono and Pistachio, which were both amazing! I wish I had more time in Charlotte to come back and try the other flavors!

Their prices are more expensive than American ice cream; 2 scoops is $7, but it is SO worth it! It is many times better than Jeni’s Splendid Ice Cream (sorry for any misspellings), and I will absolutely be back here, and in greater numbers! They do not have a lot of parking, but there are bathrooms, many beverages like espresso shots, and even a free water pitcher! Tutti Gelato is by far my favorite ice cream/gelato place and will continue to be for a long time! Please, if you are in town, stop by Tutti Gelato! Tutti gelato has been serving up delicious gelato in the heart of town. The owners are passionate about using fresh, local ingredients to create their gelato, and it shows in the taste. Tutti gelato also offers a variety of toppings, including fresh fruit, nuts, and chocolate chips.

In addition to its delicious gelato, Tutti gelato also has a warm and welcoming atmosphere. The staff is friendly and helpful, and they are always happy to chat with customers about their favorite flavors. Tutti gelato is the perfect place to stop for a quick treat on a hot day, or to enjoy a leisurely afternoon with friends.

Here are some of the things that customers love about Tutti gelato:

The gelato is made with fresh, local ingredients.

The gelato is churned slowly to create a smooth, creamy texture.

There are a wide variety of flavors to choose from.

The staff is friendly and helpful.

The atmosphere is warm and welcoming.

If you are looking for a delicious and satisfying gelato experience, then Tutti gelato is the place for you.

Creamy and delicious gelatos! We used to live in Italy, so an amazing gelato is always a great find! Whenever my husband and I visit new places, it’s a quest for us to try a highly-rated gelato establishment. I know that I would never find the same gelato here in the states as what we used to enjoy in Italy but this place comes close in decadence and silky smooth texture. It’s sweeter than its local Italian counterpart, but I think it is perfect for the average American palate. I had the Amaretto Disarono and Pistachio, which were both amazing! I wish I had more time in Charlotte to come back and try the other flavors!
I tried their Pistachio Gelato, I have never tasted such good flavors.
Delicious. 10000% better than Jeni’s.

I’m definitely going back for more.
